rComments: Not a bad teacher at all. I thought she was fair, although she wanted you to be an anthropologist as soon as you walked in the door. If you like thinking differently then this class is for you. However, this class is an easy A with the extra credit you can take. The work load is fair and only a midterm and final which are straight forward.

I loved Lindsay Bell. Although some assignments were tough, as long as you read the books, which are pretty interesting, you should be fine. She is also somewhat of a tough grader, but she offers a lot of super easy extra credit. This class was really interesting and Lindsay is super cool and funny.  I would take it again.

She is a great person and very fun and tries to make you interested in class (by bringing candy!) but she expects so much work and is an insanely hard grader. She told the class that she only gives out A's if it is exceptionally perfect. She does not care about your grade at all. Way too much work for final also! Must read a whole book in a week!

I took Dr. Bell her first semester at SUNY Oswego, she is hilarious. She is very passionate and nice, but she expects everyone to be an Anthropologist when grading, it feels impossible to get a good score. The workload is light, a lab here and there and she is very easy to contact; even has a Twitter!

Professor Bell's class is the best class I've taken during my undergrad. She is SO helpful and breaks down difficult concepts using simple terminology. Very fair and accomodates to students, not to mention kind. She goes out of her way to help students on assignments. If you have the chance to take one of her classes, definitely do. So worth it.
She's funny, helpful funky, cool and knowledgable!

Prof Bell was amazing. She knew her material and showed an obvious interest in the material, being there and working with students.  When I struggled with ideas she was more than willing to spend all the time that was needed in her office working through ideas to help me out.  Cannot thank this woman enough for all her help!
